product_title_x: Campo Viejo Rioja Reserva Red Wine 75cl
summary: Red Wine
description:
Red Wine
A complex yet approachable 2016 vintage red wine from the Spanish premier wine region Rioja, crafted by the leading winery Campo Viejo. Pairs perfectly with roast meats, grilled tuna, Sunday roasts or vegetable lasagne. This Rioja makes a great gift and is the perfect addition to any special occasion. Best served at 15 -18˚C.
The grapes used to produce this wine are fermented at a controlled temperature of around 28ºC. Maceration with skins takes place for approximately 20 days to deliver the colour of the wine. The wine is then aged for 18 months in American and French-oak casks (50:50) and rounded off for 18 months in the bottle cellar.
Tasting Notes:
A beautiful structured Spanish red wine with fruit characters such as cherries and ripe blackberries. The wine has elegant and soft tannins, middle weight, long and complex finish. A rich palate with ripe red and black fruit, subtle oaky notes with hints of liquorice and cocoa.
Won Silver in The Drinks Business Global Masters Rioja 2020.
Undoubtedly one of the best wineries in the world, Campo Viejo is located right in the heart of Rioja, Northern Spain, and is one of the leading wineries in sustainability and innovation. 100% of its electricity comes from renewable sources, and it's the first winery to be certified by Wineries for Climate Protection. Campo Viejo is committed to reduce its carbon footprint by implementing initiatives such as reducing the bottle-weight which has resulted in 30% less carbon emissions, careful water management (average water used to produce a single bottle of Campo Viejo is 0.80L as compared to the Spanish average of 2.25L) and protecting the biodiversity amongst other projects.
Campo Viejo's dedication to Spanish winemaking since 1959, alongside the most advanced winemaking techniques available, allows the winemaking team to create modern twists on traditional methods. The winery delivers progressive styles of Rioja that satisfies today's discerning modern palates and is perfect for sharing with friends. Campo Viejo is the number 1 Rioja in the world and the number 1 premium Spanish wine in the UK.
Won Silver in The Drinks Business Global Masters Rioja 2020.
Green Dot
Tidyman

JUST A FEW WARNINGS
For some people the Performa™ lubricant on these condoms can cause a rash, irritation, burning or itching. Don't get it in your eyes and wash it off after use. If you experience irritation, stop using Mutual Climax. If there's no improvement, see your doctor. Do not use these condoms if you or your partner has inflamed or broken skin.
STOP USE IMMEDIATELY AND CALL A DOCTOR: If you or your partner experiences breathing difficulties or get blue lips when using these condoms. Premature ejaculation is a common problem, which can have many causes and may require medical consultation/supervision. If these condoms don't help, it's worth checking with your doctor. Remember, no method of contraception works 100% against pregnancy, HIV or sexually transmitted infections. Condoms may present a choking hazard. Keep out of reach of children.

CONTRAINDICATIONS
This condom is made of natural rubber latex. If you have a known allergy to latex, do not use this condom as this may cause allergic reactions including anaphylactic shock.

JUST A FEW WARNINGS
STOP USE: If you feel discomfort or irritation while using condoms.
Only use a condom once.
Reuse may increase risk of failure or infection.
Condoms may present a choking hazard.
Keep out of reach of children.
If you use the condom for oral sex first, you should use a new condom for any other type of sex that follows.
Only use lubricants recommended for use with condoms.
Oil-based ones (petroleum jelly, baby oil and some pessaries) and some topical medicines that go on the penis or vagina can damage condoms.
For anal sex, use additional lubrication (do not use Durex Tingle) on the outside of the condom.

WHEN TO SEEK ADVICE
Speak to your doctor or pharmacist if you are unsure if you are allergic to latex, or if irritation or discomfort persists after use, or you are applying topical medicines to your penis or vagina. If a condom leaks or bursts during sex, consult a pharmacist or doctor as soon as possible and within 72 hours. Serious incidents must be reported to Reckitt and the local competent authority who will provide further advice. Safety and clinical performance summaries are retained by the manufacturer.

Only use lubricants recommended for use with condoms. For anal sex use additional lubrication (do not use Durex Tingle) on the outside of the condom.

To help you get it on right first time, the Durex logo on the foil shows you the bottom of the condom.

Before You Get Going
Before you use this condom, check the expiry date on the condom wrapper. If the individual container is obviously damaged, throw that one away and use a new one from an undamaged package. Put a condom on before the penis touches the other person. This helps to prevent pregnancy and the possibility of catching sexually transmitted infections during vaginal, anal or oral sex. If pregnant or breast feeding - ask a health professional before use.

How to Use Your Condom
1 Tear the wrapper open from the serrated edge. Be careful with the condom, it could get damaged by fingernails or sharp objects.
2 With the roll outside, squeeze the teat and place the condom on the tip of the erect penis.
3 Roll down to the base. If the condom doesn't unroll, it may be on backwards, discard and use a new one. Stop and check if you feel the condom slipping off or too tight on the penis because this might lead to breakage. You should take the condom off soon after ejaculation. Hold the condom firmly at the base of the penis before pulling out.
4 Throw the foil and used condom into a bin. Don't flush down the toilet.

Step 1 - Prepare: massage the Cooling Water thoroughly and let it absorb completely (at least 1min).
Step 2 - Remove: for best results, the hairs should be 2-5mm long. Slowly pull the wax strips apart. If they are too stiff, warm them briefly between your hands. Place the strip on the skin & smooth it repeatedly in the direction of hair growth. Stretch your skin and pull the wax strip off as quickly as possible parallel to the skin and against the direction of hair growth. Use the same strip repeatedly until it no longer sticks to the skin.

If your skin is irritated, use the balm only twice a week.

summary: No matter what your schedule is like, having a deodorant you can rely on will always help you feel more confident. Safety Warning:
Warnings
Do not use:
- If you are allergic to any of the ingredients
Consult your doctor before use:
- If you are taking any prescribed medicines or undergoing medical tests
- If you suffer from a chronic cough
- If you have asthma or are suffering from acute asthma attack
- If you have an intolerance to some sugars.
Contains 4.4 g of glucose per 10 ml dose.
This should be taken into account in patients with diabetes mellitus.
This medicinal product also contains ethanol, E122 and E218.
See further warnings information.

Not recommended for children under 12 years. Stop use and ask a healthcare professional if your cough lasts for more than 5 days, comes back, or is accompanied by a fever, rash or persistent headache.
Keep out of the sight and reach of children.

Further warnings
This medicinal product contains 2.4 vol% ethanol (alcohol), i.e. up to 191 mg per wine per 10 ml dose, equivalent to 4.9 ml of beer or 2ml of wine per 10 ml dose. Harmful for those suffering from alcoholism. To be taken into account in pregnant or breast-feeding women, children and high-risk groups such as patients with liver disease or epilepsy. Guaifenesin may increase the rate of absorption of paracetamol. Contains E122 - may cause allergic reactions (possibly delayed).

Side effects
If you get any of these serious side effects, stop taking the medicine. See a doctor at once:
- Difficulty in breathing, swelling of the face, neck, tongue or throat (severe allergic reactions).
These other effects are less serious. If they bother you talk to a pharmacist:
- Other allergic reactions (e.g. skin rash, red itchy skin)
- Feeling sick, being sick, stomach discomfort.

Reporting of side effects
If you get any side effects, talk to your doctor, pharmacist or nurse. This includes any possible side effects not listed on this label. You can also report side effects directly via the Yellow Card Scheme at: www.mhra.gov.uk/yellowcard or search for MHRA Yellow Card in the Google Play or Apple App Store. By reporting side effects you can help provide more information on the safety of this medicine.

Before the first use, carry out a test on a small part of the area to be waxed. For best results, the hair should be 2-5 mm long. Slowly pull the wax strips apart. If they are a little stiff, warm them briefly between your hands. Place the strip on your skin & smooth it repeatedly in the direction of the hair growth. Stretch your skin and pull the wax strip off as quickly as possible, holding it parallel to the skin and against the direction of hair growth. Upper Lips: The hair on the upper lips must be removed in two steps as it tends to grow in two directions, from the centre to the ends. Start with one side and place the strip on your skin & smooth it repeatedly in the direction of the hair growth. Stretch your skin and pull the wax strip off. Repeat on the other side of the upper lip. Don't wax the same area twice. Use the same strip repeatedly until it no longer sticks to the skin.
2. Use the Face Razor to exfoliate your skin & reveal smooth glowing skin! Keep the skin tense with one hand and with other hold the razor at 45-degree angle and glide downward on skin with short & feathery strokes. Clean blade as needed by wiping it on a cloth to remove debris.
3. Apply the multi-purpose Face Serum: it removes wax residues, moisturizes your skin & is an ideal base before putting on makeup! Massage the product with circular movements until fully absorbed.

These tips have proven themselves! Tip 1: Rinse your razor blades under running water after every shave to remove shaving foam residues and co. This prevents deposits and clogging and keeps the blades sharp longer. Tip 2: Shake your razor thoroughly after rinsing to remove excess moisture. Be careful when doing this, though. Knocking out on the edge of the sink is a taboo! The shocks can otherwise damage the structure of the blades. Consequence: you might no longer shave as thoroughly. Tip 3: Do not use a towel to dry your razor. This can dull the blades. Rather, place it in a cup.

Tip 2: For a particularly close shave, use shaving gel or soap. This also ensures that the blades of your razor glide easily over the skin, protecting against shaving irritation. Shave without pressure.

Tip 4: Replace the blades of your Wilkinson Sword razor regularly (depending on your shaving routine). If you find your blade no longer glides easily over the skin, it's time to change. Dull blades cannot shave as thoroughly and are more likely to cause skin irritation as you push harder against your skin.
